						<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Tecla Access/App</span></h1>
						<div id="bodyContent">
								<div id="siteSub">From IDRC Mobile Wiki</div>
								<div id="contentSub"><span class="subpages">&lt; <a href="/Tecla_Access" title="Tecla Access">Tecla Access</a></span></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-navigation">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:402px;"><a href="/File:Android_app_architecture.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="/images/thumb/2/22/Android_app_architecture.png/400px-Android_app_architecture.png" width="400" height="216" class="thumbimage" srcset="/images/thumb/2/22/Android_app_architecture.png/600px-Android_app_architecture.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/22/Android_app_architecture.png/800px-Android_app_architecture.png 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/File:Android_app_architecture.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>Architecture for the Android Tecla input method. The Switch Event Provider is a service that receives switch events via bluetooth from the Tecla Access Shield and broadcasts them to the OS.</div></div></div>
<p>The <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://scyp.idrc.ocad.ca/projects/tekla/the-app">Tecla Access App for Android</a> has two main software components:
</p>
<ul>
<li> The Tecla Input Method (Tecla IME) and,
</li>
<li> the <a href="/Tecla_Access/Switch_Event_Provider" title="Tecla Access/Switch Event Provider">Switch Event Provider (SEP)</a>
</li>
</ul>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><div id="toctitle"><h2>Contents</h2></div>
<ul>
